    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://www.w3schools.com/lib/w3.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons">

    <title>Uncovered</title>

</head>

<body id="page-top"git >

    <header>
        <div class="header-content">
            <div class="header-content-inner">



                  

                  <!DOCTYPE html>
                <h1 id="homeHeading">Uncovered</h1>
                <hr>
                <div style="text-align: left;">Welcome to Uncovered! This site is currently under construction and if you're here,
                you are a beta-tester. <br> <br>
                The end-goal of Uncovered is to allow people to post professional, quality photos with geo-tagging. Uncovered will be very similar to popular social media applications such as Instagram, Tumblr, and Pinterest. The idea is to convince users to locate a picture's location and use it for their own recreation. This location can then be used as a background for music videos, movie sets, photoshoots,sightseeing and more. Also, to deal with art/scenery changes, have a link or archive with “art history” that shows the history of that specific location. This will help artists promote their art, and help street art be contained and credited properly(as it gets replaced so quickly). Uncovered will ultimately bring business and add to the user’s promotional value.<br> 
<br>
At this current stage, a user can upload and delete pictures of their own, and view a log of all posts from all users. This will be the basis of my current tests before I add more content, so please feel free to sign up and test every feature available. <b>Your feedback is much appreciated!</b>
                
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section class="bg-primary" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 text-center">

                <h2>Log in</h2>

                  <%= form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: session_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
                    <div class="field">
                      <%= f.label :email %><br />
                      <%= f.email_field :email, autofocus: true %>
                    </div>

                    <div class="field">
                      <%= f.label :password %><br />
                      <%= f.password_field :password, autocomplete: "off" %>
                    </div>

                    <% if devise_mapping.rememberable? -%>
                      <div class="field">
                        <%= f.check_box :remember_me %>
                        <%= f.label :remember_me %>
                      </div>
                    <% end -%>

                    <div class="actions">
                      <%= f.submit "Log in" %>
                    </div>
                     <%= render "devise/shared/links" %>
                  <% end %>
                    <hr class="light">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <section id="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 text-center">
                    <h2 class="section-heading">Let's Get In Touch!</h2>
                    <hr class="primary">
                    <p>Want to give a detailed response of your experience? That's great! Shoot me an email or text and I will get back to you as soon as possible!</p>
                </div>

                <div class="col-lg-4 text-center">
                    <i class="fa fa-envelope-o fa-3x sr-contact"></i>
                    <p> <i class="material-icons">message</i> 786-284-1321 </p>
                    
                    <p><a href="mailto:your-email@your-domain.com">
                      <i class="material-icons">email</i>
                      wilfredoruck@gmail.com</a>
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

 

</body>

</html>

